stickerText:
Dinner for my toddler with food allergies:

Puff Pastry Salmon
recipe free of dairy, eggs, nuts, sesame
Mix together a couple Tablespoons of vegan cream cheese with steamed spinach
Spread onto a seasoned piece of salmon and wrap in a strip of thawed pastry dough
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until fish is cooked through
Rinse and dice potatoes. Cook with oil, garlic, and seasoning until crispy
We could’ve cooked this longer to get the pastry crispy but the salmon was done and my toddler was very hungry 😵‍💫
He ate sooo much! And asked for more blackberries.
